Texts.Eng: A Trink flag. I can bookmark its location so my teleporter can return me here at any time.
A Trink flag. I can use this as a waypoint for teleportation.
A locator module inside this Trink flag allows my ship's teleporter to bookmark this location.
A small locator module attached to this Trink flag allows it to be bookmarked for teleportation.
An Trink flag. I can save its location for my teleporter, allowing me to return here later.
I can bookmark this Trink flag for quick teleportin'.
The Trink Circuit's flag. Use ^green;[E]^white; to bookmark a teleportation location.
The Trink flag. My ship's teleporter can sync with its location so I can return here later.
The Trink flag. The ship's teleporter can lock on to the locator module inside it, so I can return here later.
The flag of the Trink people. My teleporter can bookmark its location for later use.
The flag of the Trink. I can save its location and return to it later using my teleporter.
This Trink flag can act as a way point, enabling me to return to this point using a teleporter.
This Trink flag can be bookmarked as a destination for my ship teleporter.
This Trink flag can be saved as a location for my teleporter. Then I can return to it any time.
Trink flag makess good point to teleport back to ussing teleporter!
Trink flag. Detected locator module. Ship teleportation system can lock on to this location.
